#. <section class="sutta" id="sn6.3"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn6.3:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 6"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 6"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn6.3:0.2"
msgid "1. Paṭhamavagga"
msgstr "1. The Appeal"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn6.3:0.3"
msgid "3. Brahmadevasutta"
msgstr "3. With Brahmadeva"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn6.3:1.1"
msgid "Evaṃ me sutaṃ—​"
msgstr "So I have heard."

msgctxt "sn6.3:1.2"
msgid ""
"ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme."
msgstr ""
"At one time the Buddha was staying near Sāvatthī in Jeta’s Grove, "
"Anāthapiṇḍika’s monastery."

msgctxt "sn6.3:1.3"
msgid ""
"Tena kho pana samayena aññatarissā brāhmaṇiyā brahmadevo nāma putto "
"bhagavato santike agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajito hoti."
msgstr ""
"Now at that time a certain brahmin lady had a son called Brahmadeva, who had "
"gone forth from the lay life to homelessness in the presence of the Buddha."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "sn6.3:2.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho āyasmā brahmadevo eko vūpakaṭṭho appamatto ātāpī pahitatto "
"viharanto nacirasseva—yassatthāya kulaputtā sammadeva agārasmā anagāriyaṃ "
"pabbajanti, tadanuttaraṃ—brahmacariyapariyosānaṃ diṭṭheva dhamme sayaṃ "
"abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja vihāsi."
msgstr ""
"Then Venerable Brahmadeva, living alone, withdrawn, diligent, keen, and "
"resolute, soon realized the supreme end of the spiritual path in this very "
"life. He lived having achieved with his own insight the goal for which "
"people from good families rightly go forth from the lay life to "
"homelessness. "

msgctxt "sn6.3:2.2"
msgid ""
"“Khīṇā jāti, vusitaṃ brahmacariyaṃ, kataṃ karaṇīyaṃ, nāparaṃ itthattāyā”ti "
"abbhaññāsi."
msgstr ""
"He understood: “Rebirth is ended; the spiritual journey has been completed; "
"what had to be done has been done; there is no return to any state of "
"existence.”"

msgctxt "sn6.3:2.3"
msgid "Aññataro ca panāyasmā brahmadevo arahataṃ ahosi."
msgstr "And Venerable Brahmadeva became one of the perfected."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts1ed" id="pts1ed1.141"></a>
#. <a class="pts2ed" id="pts2ed1.308"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "sn6.3:3.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho āyasmā brahmadevo pubbaṇhasamayaṃ nivāsetvā pattacīvaramādāya "
"sāvatthiṃ piṇḍāya pāvisi."
msgstr ""
"Then Brahmadeva robed up in the morning and, taking his bowl and robe, "
"entered Sāvatthī for alms."

msgctxt "sn6.3:3.2"
msgid ""
"Sāvatthiyaṃ sapadānaṃ piṇḍāya caramāno yena sakamātu nivesanaṃ tenupasaṅkami."
msgstr ""
"Wandering indiscriminately for alms-food in Sāvatthī, he approached his own "
"mother’s house."

msgctxt "sn6.3:3.3"
msgid ""
"Tena kho pana samayena āyasmato brahmadevassa mātā brāhmaṇī brahmuno āhutiṃ "
"niccaṃ paggaṇhāti."
msgstr ""
"Now at that time Brahmadeva’s mother, the brahmin lady, was offering up a "
"regular oblation to Brahmā."

msgctxt "sn6.3:3.4"
msgid "Atha kho brahmuno sahampatissa etadahosi:"
msgstr "Then Brahmā Sahampati thought:"

msgctxt "sn6.3:3.5"
msgid ""
"“ayaṃ kho āyasmato brahmadevassa mātā brāhmaṇī brahmuno āhutiṃ niccaṃ "
"paggaṇhāti."
msgstr ""
"“This Venerable Brahmadeva’s mother, the brahmin lady, offers up a regular "
"oblation to Brahmā."

msgctxt "sn6.3:3.6"
msgid "Yannūnāhaṃ taṃ upasaṅkamitvā saṃvejeyyan”ti."
msgstr "Why don’t I go and stir up a sense of urgency in her?”"

msgctxt "sn6.3:3.7"
msgid ""
"Atha kho brahmā sahampati—seyyathāpi nāma balavā puriso samiñjitaṃ vā bāhaṃ "
"pasāreyya, pasāritaṃ vā bāhaṃ samiñjeyya; evameva—brahmaloke antarahito "
"āyasmato brahmadevassa mātu nivesane pāturahosi."
msgstr ""
"Then, as easily as a strong person would extend or contract their arm, he "
"vanished from the Brahmā realm and reappeared in the house of Brahmadeva’s "
"mother."

msgctxt "sn6.3:3.8"
msgid ""
"Atha kho brahmā sahampati vehāsaṃ ṭhito āyasmato brahmadevassa mātaraṃ "
"brāhmaṇiṃ gāthāya ajjhabhāsi:"
msgstr ""
"Then Brahmā Sahampati, while standing in the air, addressed Brahmadeva’s "
"mother in verse:"

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "sn6.3:4.1"
msgid "“Dūre ito brāhmaṇi brahmaloko,"
msgstr "“Far from here is the Brahmā realm, madam,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn6.3:4.2"
msgid "Yassāhutiṃ paggaṇhāsi niccaṃ;"
msgstr "to which you offer a regular oblation."

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn6.3:4.3"
msgid "Netādiso brāhmaṇi brahmabhakkho,"
msgstr "But Brahmā doesn’t eat that kind of food."

#. <br>
#. VAR: ajānaṃ → ajānantī (bj, pts1, mr)
msgctxt "sn6.3:4.4"
msgid "Kiṃ jappasi brahmapathaṃ ajānaṃ."
msgstr "Why make invocations, when you don’t know the path to Brahmā?"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "sn6.3:5.1"
msgid "Eso hi te brāhmaṇi brahmadevo,"
msgstr "This Brahmadeva, madam,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn6.3:5.2"
msgid "Nirūpadhiko atidevapatto;"
msgstr "free of attachments, has surpassed the gods."

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn6.3:5.3"
msgid "Akiñcano bhikkhu anaññaposī,"
msgstr "A mendicant without possessions or dependents,"

#. <br>
#. VAR: so → te so (pts1) | yo te sa (?)
msgctxt "sn6.3:5.4"
msgid "Yo te so piṇḍāya gharaṃ paviṭṭho."
msgstr "he has entered your house for alms."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts2ed" id="pts2ed1.309"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "sn6.3:6.1"
msgid "Āhuneyyo vedagu bhāvitatto,"
msgstr ""
"He’s worthy of offerings dedicated to the gods, a knowledge master, self-"
"developed."

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn6.3:6.2"
msgid "Narānaṃ devānañca dakkhiṇeyyo;"
msgstr "He’s worthy of a teacher’s offering from gods and men."

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn6.3:6.3"
msgid "Bāhitvā pāpāni anūpalitto,"
msgstr "Having shunned all evils, he’s unsullied."

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn6.3:6.4"
msgid "Ghāsesanaṃ iriyati sītibhūto."
msgstr "Cool at heart, he wanders looking for food."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc7"></a>
msgctxt "sn6.3:7.1"
msgid "Na tassa pacchā na puratthamatthi,"
msgstr "He has no before and after,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn6.3:7.2"
msgid "Santo vidhūmo anigho nirāso;"
msgstr "peaceful, unclouded, untroubled, with no need for hope,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn6.3:7.3"
msgid "Nikkhittadaṇḍo tasathāvaresu,"
msgstr "he has laid down the rod for all creatures firm and frail."

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn6.3:7.4"
msgid "So tyāhutiṃ bhuñjatu aggapiṇḍaṃ."
msgstr "So let him enjoy your offering of choice alms."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc8"></a>
msgctxt "sn6.3:8.1"
msgid "Visenibhūto upasantacitto,"
msgstr "With peaceful mind, he has left the crowd,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn6.3:8.2"
msgid "Nāgova danto carati anejo;"
msgstr "he wanders like a tamed elephant, unperturbed."

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn6.3:8.3"
msgid "Bhikkhu susīlo suvimuttacitto,"
msgstr "He’s a mendicant fair in ethics, with heart well freed."

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn6.3:8.4"
msgid "So tyāhutiṃ bhuñjatu aggapiṇḍaṃ."
msgstr "So let him enjoy your offering of choice alms."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts1ed" id="pts1ed1.142"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc9"></a>
msgctxt "sn6.3:9.1"
msgid "Tasmiṃ pasannā avikampamānā,"
msgstr "With unwavering confidence in him,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn6.3:9.2"
msgid "Patiṭṭhapehi dakkhiṇaṃ dakkhiṇeyye;"
msgstr "present your teacher’s offering to one who deserves it."

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn6.3:9.3"
msgid "Karohi puññaṃ sukhamāyatikaṃ,"
msgstr "Now that you’ve seen the sage who has crossed over, madam,"

# This obviously represents the end of Brahma’s speech. What follows is according to the commentaries added by redactors.
#. <br>
msgctxt "sn6.3:9.4"
msgid "Disvā muniṃ brāhmaṇi oghatiṇṇanti."
msgstr "make merit for the sake of future happiness!”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts2ed" id="pts2ed1.310"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc10"></a>
msgctxt "sn6.3:10.1"
msgid "Tasmiṃ pasannā avikampamānā,"
msgstr "With unwavering confidence in him,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn6.3:10.2"
msgid "Patiṭṭhapesi dakkhiṇaṃ dakkhiṇeyye;"
msgstr "she presented her teacher’s offering to one who deserved it."

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn6.3:10.3"
msgid "Akāsi puññaṃ sukhamāyatikaṃ,"
msgstr "After seeing the sage who had crossed over, the brahmin lady"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn6.3:10.4"
msgid "Disvā muniṃ brāhmaṇī oghatiṇṇan”ti."
msgstr "made merit for the sake of future happiness."
